<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="2117" pageId="20" pageNumber="2116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1155,1615,1709]" box="[160,276,1615,1640]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2116">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1155,1615,1709]" lastBlockId="21.[160,1156,972,1134]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="2117" pageId="20" pageNumber="2116">
This species is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gong &amp; Chen, 2018" authorityName="Gong &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2018" box="[571,741,1649,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Pseudostegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="2116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montipagana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[571,741,1649,1674]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2116">P. montipagana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[747,832,1650,1674]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the wing pattern and male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[283,391,1685,1709]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="21.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 12. Pseudostegana sigangli sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (b, c) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="20" pageNumber="2116">Figure 12</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished from it by the ocellar triangle, scutum and aedeagus; in this species, ocellar triangle narrowly elongated to anterior margin of frons (
<figureCitation box="[166,259,1006,1030]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 5. Head, thorax, wing and abdomen of male: (a–f) Pseudostegana montipagana sp. nov.; (g–l) P. sigangli sp. nov." pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(j)); scutum yellow on anterior two-thirds, brownish yellow on posterior one-third (
<figureCitation box="[166,259,1041,1065]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 5. Head, thorax, wing and abdomen of male: (a–f) Pseudostegana montipagana sp. nov.; (g–l) P. sigangli sp. nov." pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(k)); aedeagus apically acute in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[747,854,1041,1065]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="21.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 12. Pseudostegana sigangli sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (b, c) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 12</figureCitation>
(c)). The 10.6% interspecific genetic distance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gong &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2018" box="[373,544,1075,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Pseudostegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montipagana">
<emphasis box="[373,544,1075,1100]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">P. montipagana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the smallest within this group; there are 12 diagnostic sites between 
<taxonomicName authority="Gong &amp; Chen, 2018" authorityName="Gong &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2018" box="[319,428,1109,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Pseudostegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sigangli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[319,428,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">P. sigangli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[434,520,1110,1134]" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gong &amp; Chen, 2018" authorityName="Gong &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2018" box="[575,747,1109,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Pseudostegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montipagana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[575,747,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">P. montipagana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[753,839,1110,1134]" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[851,945,1110,1134]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 2. Diagnostic nucleotide sites in the alignment of the COI sequences of the genus Pseudostegana. Numbers at the top show the positions of the sites in the COI alignment (656–684 bp in length). Shaded sites are diagnostic for each species. Dashes (−) indicate missing data." pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" startId="21.[160,225,121,144]">
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1160,120,202]" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,264,121,144]" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gong &amp; Chen, 2018" authorityName="Gong &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2018" box="[273,498,120,143]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Pseudostegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sigangli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[273,498,120,143]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Pseudostegana sigangli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,587,121,144]" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (b, c) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="2118" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1156,1179,1550]" box="[160,294,1179,1204]" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1156,1179,1550]" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,224,1214,1239]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Male.</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[313,408,1214,1238]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 5. Head, thorax, wing and abdomen of male: (a–f) Pseudostegana montipagana sp. nov.; (g–l) P. sigangli sp. nov." pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(g,j)): Ocellar triangle and frons brownish. Pedicel and first flagellomere yellow. Face brown. Palpus yellow, broadened in male, medially one-third as wide as long. Clypeus black. Gena brown. Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[621,714,1284,1308]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 5. Head, thorax, wing and abdomen of male: (a–f) Pseudostegana montipagana sp. nov.; (g–l) P. sigangli sp. nov." pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(h,k)): Pleura nearly brown. Katepisternal setae three. Scutellum brownish, pale at tip. Legs: Yellow, brownish on basal half of tibiae of mid and hind legs. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[514,612,1353,1377]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 5. Head, thorax, wing and abdomen of male: (a–f) Pseudostegana montipagana sp. nov.; (g–l) P. sigangli sp. nov." pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(l)): All tergites nearly black. Sternites yellow on second and third, brownish to dark brown on the rest. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1145,1388,1412]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="21.[160,225,121,144]" captionText="Figure 12. Pseudostegana sigangli sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (b, c) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">Figure 12</figureCitation>
): Epandrium roundly protruding on ventral margin, with about 17 setae per side. Surstylus protruding on posteroventral corner. Cercus ventrally round. Paramere apically bifurcated, subapically with two long sensilla and several sensilla on dorsal projection. Basal process of aedeagus slender, apically about six finger-like projections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1156,1595,1689]" box="[160,333,1595,1620]" pageId="21" pageNumber="2117">
